Suggested Order for Syntax Explanation
Basic Syntax (comments, whitespace, statements).

Types (primitives, composites, special types).

Variables and Constants.

Control Flow (conditionals, loops, branching).

Functions (declaration, invocation, lambdas, overloading).

Objects (classes, encapsulation, inheritance, polymorphism).

Memory Management (allocation, deallocation, references).

Modules and Packages (imports, exports).

Exception Handling (try-catch-throw).

Concurrency (threads, task API).

Standard Libraries (collections, I/O, serialization, utilities).

Advanced Features (generics, user-defined types, pointers).

